<TITLE> New district council act to be tabled next session: minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 29 (bdnews24.com)  Local government and rural development minister Syed Ashraful Islam on Wednesday said a new district council act will be tabled in the next parliament session. "It will be enacted after parliamentary approval," he said on the second day of a three-day council of deputy commissioners, who are the district level chief executives. He said the local government ministry has already marked twenty discrepancies in the implementation of the current district council law. "New draft laws on delineating the power of UP chairman, vice-chairman and upazila nirbahi officers will also be presented in parliament very soon," said Ashraf. He also added that the local government ministry has finalised a proposal for doubling the pay of village police. He said the proposal was under consideration of the finance ministry. Presently they are paid Tk 1700 a month. bd
